docuseries.title: Docuseries
docuseries.description: Truth is stranger than fiction in these shows that span history, science, nature, and more.

0300006999.title: Bizarre Murders
0300006999.description: Told by former detectives through vivid re-enactments, hear stories of true crimes committed by the unlikely and that border on the outlandish.

0300004774.title: Dr. G: Medical Examiner
0300004774.description: Mysterious causes of death that don't make visible sense are the focus of this series with expert explanations and theories by a famous coroner.

0300006582.title: 21st Century Serial Killer
0300006582.description: An unflinching look at some of the most heinous crimes of our modern times, as discussed by victim’s family members and forensic experts.

04598.title: Baby Animals in the Wild
04598.description: A playfully narrated look at a day in the life of a range of adorable baby animal species in their natural environments around the globe.

04469.title: Secret Eaters
04469.description: Anna Richardson will expose the country’s secret eating habits, one household at a time to help people who are mystified as to why they’re piling on the pounds.

04178.title: Murderous Minds
04178.description: From Jack the Ripper to Ted Bundy and the Columbine shooters, here’s a look at the negative, horrific catalysts that create savage serial killers.

0300007832.title: Deadly Australia
0300007832.description: This documentary is an exploration of how Australia’s deadliest animals are inspiring cutting edge research in biomedicine and biotechnology.

0300009129.title: Building Paradise Island
0300009129.description: From first foundations to the opening party, the amazing story of the transformation of an abandoned, industrial island into a luxury destination.

0300010136.title: Navy SEALs BUD/S Class 234
0300010136.description: Follow Class 234 as they struggle to make it through BUD/S, the Navy’s grueling selection course for America’s most elite force, the SEALs.

0167.title: The FBI Files
0167.description: This documentary reality series takes viewers behind the scenes of major crime investigations, as agents and scientists recount their forensic detective work.

0300007501.title: 1945-1953: From World War to Cold War
0300007501.description: At the outset of the Yalta Conference on February 4, 1945, the "Big Three" were optimistic: the accord that they had achieved seemed to hold strong.

03128.title: Warbirds Over the Trenches
03128.description: This is the story of the beginning of war in the sky! Discover the legendary aircrafts and thrilling aerial battles that marked many historic achievements and advances for pilots, engineers and our military. Through captivating final interviews with some of the men who flew in the Great War, incredible film footage of the aircraft they flew and video of restored aircraft still flying 100 years later, this one-of-a-kind collection allows you to experience history's soaring military transformations like never before!

0300010364.title: The Atlanta Child Murders
0300010364.description: Chronicles the cold case involving 29 African American children who went missing and were later found dead in Atlanta between 1979 and 1981.

0300010350.title: O.J. & Nicole: An American Tragedy
0300010350.description: In this engaging true-crime series, Tanya Brown, sister of Nicole Simpson, tells her sister's side of the story using Nicole's own words.

0300007177.title: The Nature of Existence Companion Series
0300007177.description: A deep dive into the most challenging topics and philosophical questions from the original film with over 100 experts from all over the world.

03587.title: I Survived
03587.description: Ordinary people in deadly circumstances, from nightmarish abductions to shocking accidents, tell the incredible stories of how they survived.

0300006732.title: Bloodline Detectives
0300006732.description: A compelling 20-part series, hosted by a preeminent legal analyst and renowned former prosecutor, explores the advanced form of familial DNA testing.

04700.title: Crime Stories With Nancy Grace
04700.description: FOX Nation's Nancy Grace dives deep into the day's most shocking crimes and asks the tough questions with honest perspective you won't get anywhere else.

0300010021.title: Dead Famous DNA
0300010021.description: Mark Evans sets out to track down the remains of history's most famous figures and attempts to solve the mysteries that have persisted around them.

0300008886.title: Dark Side of the Ring: Confidential
0300008886.description: What’s at the heart of wrestling's mysterious past? A fascinating look back at the most shocking stories from the sport’s previous 40 years.

0300010320.title: Murder Comes to Town
0300010320.description: Friends and family recount personal stories of horrific crimes that took place in some of the most unassuming places throughout America's heartland.

03935.title: Murders of Cape Town
03935.description: A gut-wrenching documentary-crime series that follows the individual cases of three brutal murders that rocked Cape Town, South Africa over the years.

0300010317.title: Southern Fried Homicide
0300010317.description: Serving up salacious true crime stories from south of the Mason-Dixon Line, this series shows the evil that can lurk behind Southern hospitality.

03555.title: 101 People Who Made the 20th Century
03555.description: Counting down the key figures of the 20th century, this series profiles the political leaders, scientists and artists who shaped the world today.

03440.title: The Story of J.R.R. Tolkien: Master of the Rings
03440.description: The life of “The Lord of the Rings” universe creator J.R.R. Tolkien, and how his life and experience in World War I informed his epic storytelling.

0300010329.title: Murder Comes Home
0300010329.description: Pairing footage from crime scenes with real home video, this series explores and unravels intimate and emotionally powerful mysteries.

03685.title: 60 Days In
03685.description: Innocent volunteers are sent to prison for 60 days, without officers or inmates knowing their secret, offering an unfiltered look at life behind bars.

0300004871.title: Murder Made Me Famous
0300004871.description: An in-depth look at killers who gained public notoriety when their crimes received media attention.

0300006901.title: The Ascent of Woman: A 10,000 Year Story
0300006901.description: Historians, authors, and experts on a variety of subjects illuminate the ways women have made and changed human history from 10,000 B.C. to this day.

0300010094.title: Philadelphia Experiment
0300010094.description: In 1943, a U.S. Navy ship vanishes and travels through time during a secret World War II experiment gone wrong, setting off a series of events.

0300008132.title: Reclaiming the Throne
0300008132.description: This doc takes a detailed dive into Biblical prophecies, as well as historical and scientific research about the Children of Israel’s identity.

0300008074.title: I Bought a Rainforest
0300008074.description: A documentary that takes on the passionate journey of a wildlife photographer who buys his own parcel of land in Peru’s incredible Amazon rainforest.

0300004913.title: Mafia Killers
0300004913.description: Colin McLaren shares stories about his undercover work inside organized crime families; chilling firsthand details about how mafia families operate and why their ruthlessness was often their downfall.

0300010324.title: The Haunted
0300010324.description: Pet parents recount their animals' chilling experiences with ghosts, demons and other paranormal phenomena happening in their households.

0300008791.title: Great Kings of England
0300008791.description: Fascinating re-enactments show how Alfred, King of Wessex secured England and built a fierce naval fleet after being devastated by Viking invasions.

0300005588.title: Anthony Bourdain: A Cook's Tour
0300005588.description: Join Anthony Bourdain in his groundbreaking first series as he travels around the world indulging his taste for local cuisine and eccentric characters.

0300009103.title: Into the Wild Frontier
0300009103.description: Early pioneers, scouts, hunters, and traders fulfill America's destiny to expand West, exploring uncharted territory to blaze new trails.

0300010368.title: Killing Richard Glossip
0300010368.description: The legal team of a man sitting on death in Oklahoma for a crime he swears he didn’t commit races against time to uncover evidence to exonerate him.

04140.title: Museum Secrets
04140.description: In every episode, Museum Secrets travels to one extraordinary museum, revealing the stories of 6 irreplaceable treasures, probing familiar legends and assumptions, using cutting edge research and technology to investigate the unknown. Museum Secrets combines surprising revelations about things we all recognize with amazing revelations about things we’ve never seen before.

0300004878.title: The Price of Fame
0300004878.description: The road to stardom is often paved with amazing and devastating public and private events.

0300010321.title: Mysteries at the Monument
0300010321.description: Host Don Wildman uncovers incredible tales of crimes, scandals, and disasters tied to iconic structures, statues, and national parks.

03125.title: National Parks Exploration Series
03125.description:
"A Virtual Tour of America's Greatest Attractions!

The exquisite National Parks Exploration Series takes viewers on a guided tour across the most visited and significant parks in the United States. Discover the wonder and mystery of these parks and enjoy hours of breathtaking beauty and exploration of our country's most fascinating destinations!"

0300007794.title: TMZ Investigates: Tiger King - What Really Went Down?
0300007794.description: A behind-the-scenes look at the true-crime story involving Joe Exotic's murder-for-hire plot and the disappearance of Carole Baskin's husband.

0300008842.title: A&E: After Dark
0300008842.description: Get an insider’s perspective of Hull Royal Infirmary, where staff members in the Accident and Emergency Department face never-ending challenges.

0300005198.title: Arnhem 1944: A Bridge Too Far Collection
0300005198.description: A rare and extensive collection of footage from the 9-day battle in the Netherlands during WWII where German forces overtook British Allied troops.

03344.title: Wild Animal Rescue
03344.description: Wild animals are under threat across the globe, and workers from Four Paws go on daring and dangerous missions to give them a better life.

03899.title: Battle 360
03899.description: Learn all about the USS Enterprise aircraft carrier and the critical role in played in some of the fiercest World War II battles.

0300008119.title: Great Queens of England
0300008119.description: A look at the queens of England since 1066, including Empress Matild, Lady Jane Grey, Elizabeth I and Elizabeth II, and Queen Mary I and Mary II.

03644.title: Waco: Madman or Messiah
03644.description: Cult survivors, news clips and recordings of the dangerous, charismatic "prophet" chronicle the 51-day standoff between David Koresh and the FBI.

04131.title: Hitler’s Propaganda Machine
04131.description: Power, terror, performance. These notions define our perception of Adolf Hitler and the Nazi Party at the height of the Third Reich. But behind these impressions Hitler was a rather ordinary man. This compelling new series tells the story of one of the most comprehensive, wide-reaching, and successful marketing campaigns in modern history. It describes in a whole new way the rise of Adolf Hitler.

0300010040.title: Serial Killer With Piers Morgan
0300010040.description: In this thrilling series, television personality Piers Morgan meets and interviews some of America’s most depraved serial killers.

0300010294.title: Murder in Paradise
0300010294.description: This reality series looks into dream getaways that were torn apart by the true stories of shocking and horrific murders that took place there.

0300006217.title: Wildlife Icons
0300006217.description: From close-knit communities of hamadryas baboons to graceful herds of springbok, get an intimate look at some of Africa’s most remarkable wildlife.

0300009740.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life
0300009740.description: There is no shortage of experts on Hitler’s sex life who consider the dictator’s predilections to be a barometer of his twisted psyche and behavior.

0300005171.title: Forensic Investigators
0300005171.description: True case histories from infamous and bizarre murder cases in Australia, ranging from heroin heists and personal assassinations to adult kidnappings.

0300007226.title: Behind Bars: The World's Toughest Prisons
0300007226.description: Imagine prisons so tough that even the hardest gang bosses and killers learn the meaning of fear. This extraordinary series is an intimate portrait of crime and punishment that goes beyond the gates, walls, barred windows and cells of the world's toughest maximum security prisons. From Bolivia to Bulgaria, Dallas to Arizona, enter a world of hardened criminals and prisoners that few ever glimpse.

03909.title: The World Wars
03909.description: Historical documentary that tracks the assassination in Sarajevo that sparked World War I up through the next global battle that was World War II.

0300000050.title: Exploration Volcano
0300000050.description: Volcanologist Chris Horsley travels to worldwide destinations to respond to volcanic eruptions that threaten to wreak havoc and destroy communities.

0300007661.title: The Innocence Network
0300007661.description: Follow the work of nonprofit organizations that review flagged criminal cases and help to exonerate incarcerated people deemed wrongly convicted.

0300009736.title: The Rising
0300009736.description: This is an inspiring documentary series that celebrates the contributions and achievements of Black athletes from around the world.

04818.title: Beyond Belief: Fact or Fiction
04818.description: A series of logic defying stories about supernatural and psychic phenomenon challenge viewers to determine which are truth and which are fiction.

0300004897.title: Sex Lies & Murder
0300004897.description: Greed, lies and love triangles lead to crimes of passion that turn simple breakups into headline-grabbing stories with life-changing consequences.

03503.title: Special Delivery: Baby ER
03503.description: True stories of babies, their parents, doctors and caregivers in a neonatal Intensive care unit, as babies receive immediate, life-saving care.

01763.title: America's 60 Greatest Unsolved Mysteries and Crimes
01763.description: This compelling documentary series presents a countdown of America's 60 most notorious unsolved mysteries and crimes in a dramatic compilation revealing these unanswered questions in 10 fascinating episodes.

04768.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds
04768.description: Part Three of the Emmy-winning series, written and directed by the late Carl Sagan’s wife and hosted by his protege, explores our wondrous universe.

0300009451.title: British Railway Journeys
0300009451.description: There's no better way to enjoy the enchanting beauty of Britain than by rail, so hop aboard some of England's most charming train rides.

0300005860.title: Ambulance Australia
0300005860.description: A docuseries that looks into the hearts and souls of the emergency workers devoted to helping others on the worst day of their lives.

0300010297.title: Murder Among Friends
0300010297.description: While most killers act alone, the truth of who did it becomes a strange puzzle when groups conspire to commit murder.

04248.title: Crate Diggers
04248.description: Iconic DJ’s use their passion for vinyl records to spark memories and personal conversations between the artists and the lovers of their music.

0300009612.title: Caught in the Act
0300009612.description: This captivating nature documentary series features footage of wildlife caught in the act of being raw, uninhibited, and wild in the outdoors.

0300009747.title: The Listening Road
0300009747.description: This docu-series captures one man’s remarkable 33-day journey cycling 3,000 miles across the U.S. to engage with people from all walks of life.

0300007010.title: Mayday: Air Disasters
0300007010.description: This series takes a detailed look at aviation disasters to discover what went wrong using actual recordings, reports, and eyewitness accounts.

0300010302.title: Too Cute!
0300010302.description: This series tells the coming-of-age stories of cuddly baby animals, from their wobbly first steps to their first venture into the outside world.

02410.title: Danger Dogs
02410.description: Rescue dogs are given a second chance and put through a rigorous training routine to prepare for life as an elite canine, protecting society from drugs and explosives.

0300006824.title: Helicopter Warfare
0300006824.description: An examination of the bravery of helicopter crews, who went on missions to save lives in Vietnam, Falklands, Afghanistan, and the Iraq wars.

01756.title: Vietnam: 50 Years Remembered
01756.description: In 1965, the United States officially became involved in the conflict in Southeast Asia, where decades of turmoil had been building since the beginning of World War II. The fall of French Indochina and the spread of Communism catapulted the country into one of its longest and deadliest wars. The history of U.S. involvement in Vietnam is told in this 7-part documentary series. Featuring personal stories from veterans and detailing the battles, strategy, and politics of a war that consumed multiple U.S. Presidents. Vietnam: 50 Years Remembered is a chronicle of the tragedy that tested the strength of our country and forever changed the social and political landscape of the world.

0300007447.title: The World's Strangest Mysteries
0300007447.description: Footage of UFO's, mysterious anomalies, paranormal sightings, weird discoveries in space, and bizarre case files form a library of the unexplainable.

0518.title: Booze Britain
0518.description: Documents the binge drinking culture of various towns and cities in the United Kingdom.

03881.title: Weird or What? With William Shatner
03881.description: William Shatner hosts this investigative series that explores the world's most puzzling mysteries and logic-defying phenomena in search of answers.

0300007809.title: TMZ Investigates: UFOs: The Pentagon Proof
0300007809.description: Unpack the first-ever declassified Pentagon report detailing 144 accounts of UFO sightings, including new footage released from a USS naval ship.

0300006233.title: Slender Man Stabbing: The Untold Story
0300006233.description: The disturbing story of how an Internet meme about a fictional supernatural character coerced two 12-year-old girls to brutally murder their friend.

0300007201.title: Ancient Planet Trilogy
0300007201.description: This trilogy consists of 3 x 30 HD episodes that cover the history of our planet and the most ancient life on it during the Hadean, Archean and Proterozoic eons (from 4.6 billion years ago until 500 million years ago

03061.title: Quest for the Bay
03061.description: In this five part "living history" series about eight "average people" (7 men and one women) who volunteer to relive an adventure. The epic 1200 kilometer journey by the Hudson's Bay Company fur traders of 1840s from Winnipeg, to the Hudson Bay. They undertake this grueling and difficult journey through the heart of the Canadian wilderness in a historically accurate York Boat. Rowing 12 to 14 hours a day, carrying 180 lb. packs, shooting the rapids, and covering over 1200 kilometers, the trip will take eight to twelve weeks

03651.title: Babies Behind Bars
03651.description: Imprisoned mothers are given the unique opportunity to raise their babies behind bars. But rules are strict, and one slip-up can take it all away.

0300008107.title: Best Battles Rallies
0300008107.description: This enjoyable collection of some of the closest-fought contests from the archives of racing promises to make you feel the heat of the competition.

0300006442.title: Forensics
0300006442.description: This fascinating docuseries explores New Zealand's most puzzling crimes, which investigators hope that forensic science will finally solve.

0300008884.title: Donkmaster
0300008884.description: Catch all the excitement of big rim racing from Florida to Baton Rouge, where drivers compete for a title and thousands of dollars.

0300009716.title: Boston George: Famous Without the Fortune (Sub Esp)
0300009716.description: A docu-series about the life of George Jung, who spent much of his life indulging in the chase as a drug trafficker during the 1970s and 1980s.

0300010325.title: The 1980s: The Deadliest Decade
0300010325.description: The 1980s: A time of fast living, glamor, and greed. This series recounting murder investigations reveals the dark side of the decade.

0300010323.title: Village of the Damned
0300010323.description: Examines the strange string of murders that have stalked the people of the quaint town of Dryden, New York—a place that some would say is cursed.

0300006229.title: WWII Dambusters: RAF Raid on Germany
0300006229.description: On the 60th anniversary of Operation Chastise, British engineers and pilots recreate the precision it took to destroy a series of crucial German dams.

0300004748.title: Face of the World: Mapping Our History
0300004748.description: From Marco Polo’s journey through China to the borders of the Roman Empire, this series charts how humans traveled around the planet.

0300007872.title: Cruise Ship Killers
0300007872.description: A true crime docuseries that takes on the personal stories and cases of people whose cruise ship vacations ended in death before they came home.

0300007779.title: Meet, Marry, Murder
0300007779.description: Wedded couples vow to stay together, until death do they part. This series looks at what happens when a bride or groom causes their beloved’s demise.

0300000131.title: Cirque Du Soleil: Spotlight On
0300000131.description: Watch the acrobats and artists of Cirque du Soleil as they perform thrilling acts from seven of Cirque du Soleil's most popular shows.

0300005207.title: History of the Korean War
0300005207.description: Color footage and U.S. military films illustrate the 3-year Korean War’s horrific combat toll, starting with North Korea’s advance into South Korea.

04541.title: The Silk Road
04541.description: Join Alfred de Montesquiou, a war correspondent, as he travels through six countries and cultures, delving into their rich histories.

0300008661.title: Genealogy Roadshow
0300008661.description: This fascinating television show borrows from elements of history and science to explore the background of various Americans, revealing many insights.

0300009127.title: Lisa Evers: Crime and Hip Hop
0300009127.description: New York crime and investigative reporter Lisa Evers probes the murders of three of the most significant hip hop artists of the last decade.

01058.title: Ocean Wilds
01058.description: In the spectacular and lyrical five-part series, award-winning filmmaker Feodor Pitcairns images and personal observations offer a fresh vision of life in the sea. Nearly a decade in the making, the films convey the powerful immediacy in the sea  revealing a world of unique moods and movements, of brilliant colours and striking light patterns, of curious creatures and extraordinary phenomena.

0300006209.title: Secrets of the Middle Earth: Inside Tolkien's Lord of the Rings
0300006209.description: Interviews, fantastical art, and the latest advanced mapping techniques deliver the themes, influences, and magic that shaped the author's epic work.

03924.title: Intervention
03924.description: Emmy-Award winning series of profiles in addiction, with backstories and the current crisis that brings about family intervention and hope in rehab.

0300006533.title: Travel Man: 48 Hours In…
0300006533.description: Comic Richard Ayoade and guests show us where we go wrong, by having the most culturally efficient holiday possible, with every boring bit removed.

0300005802.title: Body Cam Cops
0300005802.description: Actual riveting footage of law enforcement surveillance reveals harrowing chases and dangerous fights with criminals on the streets.

04114.title: Hunt Co
04114.description: The HuntCo crew goes turkey hunting in Texas, deer hunting in Canada, bow fishing in the Ozarks, whitetail hunting in Missouri, and search for a giant buck named "Cocaine".

04057.title: Jo Frost: Nanny on Tour
04057.description: The renowned English nanny travels through US cities to help families who need to work on communication, discipline, and respect.

0300005587.title: Secrets of the National Parks
0300005587.description: Unearth the secrets of some of America’s most profound national parks, and discover the importance of preserving and conserving our Earth’s wild lands.

0300007945.title: Iron Chef
0300007945.description: Catch all the excitement of a sporting event mixed with the skill and passion required to create an innovative culinary masterpiece.

0300005635.title: I Shouldn’t Be Alive
0300005635.description: Gripping re-enactments of true tales of survival against extraordinary odds, from dangerous elements to grueling psychological circumstances.

0300006574.title: Jefferson Davis: An American President
0300006574.description: An examination of the Confederate States of America’s first and only president: from his early life, to his work as an army officer and more.

0300005343.title: Drive Thru History: The Gospels
0300005343.description: A faith-based travel show teaching the story of Jesus by visiting 50 ancient sites in Israel recorded in the Gospels of Matthew, Mark, Luke and John.

0300008066.title: Extreme E Specials
0300008066.description: Extreme E Specials highlight the thrill of electric SUV racing around the world with the crucial benefit of climate change mindfulness.

01731.title: 24 Hours in A&E
01731.description: Cameras film around the clock in some of Britain's busiest A&E departments.

01056.title: End of the Big Cats
01056.description: Can you imagine a life without Lions, Cheetahs and Leopards? Fifty years ago, there were more than half a million lions in Africa. Today there are fewer than 20,000. A world without these majestic predators could soon become a reality. This series gives a new perspective on the problems suffered by the big cats in this changing era in Africa. With the illegal and legal hunting ever prevalent, will society listen to how they can keep these cats alive?

0524.title: The New Detectives
0524.description: World-renowned forensics experts and criminal investigators solve murders and other crimes.

0300007978.title: Best Battles Motocross
0300007978.description: Get ready for your jaw to drop to the floor after viewing this collection of the closest fought races in motocross! The action never stops.

0300004874.title: Crime Stories
0300004874.description: Crime Stories chronicles some of the most intriguing crimes in history. This investigative series takes the viewers behind the yellow tape, revealing what occurred, introducing the people involved, unveiling techniques used in solving the crime, exposing the emotion experienced by those affected, and the final resolution of the case.

0300005798.title: World's Worst Flights
0300005798.description: Themed episodes, packed with spine-tingling action and revealing insight into the world of commercial flight, show what happens when things go wrong.

0300010332.title: The 93 Victims of Samuel Little
0300010332.description: An FBI crime analyst, a DOJ forensics expert and a Texas Ranger open a Pandora’s box of horrors while prying a confession out of a serial killer.

0300009918.title: Murdered at First Sight
0300009918.description: This chilling and fascinating British true crime series tells the shocking stories of people murdered by someone they had never met.

04037.title: The American West
04037.description: Robert Redford’s documentary series about the growth of the West in the U.S. from 1865 to 1890, including the true stories behind historic legends.

0300004702.title: Hoarders: Buried Alive in My Bedroom
0300004702.description: Extreme cases of hoarding are shown, whether it’s refusing to throw away old food or living in bowel waste, and how the problem is on the rise.

0300006750.title: Penguins on a Plane: Great Animal Moves
0300006750.description: The hit BBC series about how  caring and expert animal handlers help fly precious animals, from penguins to a hippo, to their new environments.

03589.title: America's War on Drugs
03589.description: An immersive trip through five decades of American drug policy, this docuseries probes the unintended consequences of criminalizing narcotics.

0300006276.title: Living With Volcanoes
0300006276.description: A fascinating and colorful look at the ways more than 500 million people adjust to life in the shadow of essential, yet potentially deadly, volcanoes.

02914.title: Forensic Files
02914.description: Witnesses, investigators and medical experts lend their unique perspective on true crime in every episode of this long-running docuseries.

01051.title: Asia's Monarchies
01051.description: In this five-part series we journey to the heart of these beautiful lands to understand the relationship between the Asian people and their monarchs.

0300010223.title: Who Killed the Lyon Sisters?
0300010223.description: Sisters Katherine and Sheila Lyon vanish from a shopping mall in the Washington, D.C. suburbs, launching a 40-year search for the truth.

0300007323.title: Aliens & UFO's - Visitors From Beyond
0300007323.description: Thousands of people from all walks of life have witnessed UFOs, but many remain silent through fear of being ridiculed. The fact is, what modern man is experiencing is not new. Vivid accounts of UFO phenomena have been passed down from the most ancient of times, stating that not only were there visitors from another world, but they gave humanity a vast array of knowledge.

0300005909.title: The Amazing World of Aviation
0300005909.description: Starting with the Wright Brothers in 1903, civil aviation has transformed into a multi-billion dollar industry full of endless possibilities.

0300008190.title: Dark Side of the Ring
0300008190.description: The acclaimed docuseries that takes on the dark history and struggles of some of world wrestling’s most notorious fighters and their private ordeals.

0300005436.title: MTB Heroes
0300005436.description: Hit the trail with this series dedicated to mountain biking, introducing the best riders and following them in their daily lives around the world.

0300009263.title: While the Rest of Us Die: Secrets of America's Shadow Government
0300009263.description: The secret history of the U.S. government's doomsday plans from the Cold War to COVID-19 reveals that maybe it’s time to rethink everything.

0300004773.title: Dr. G: America's Most Shocking Cases
0300004773.description: A famed coroner takes on shocking cases of notable and mysterious deaths that may reveal more than meets the eye in this investigative series.

0300006356.title: Alien Autopsy
0300006356.description: Jonathan Frakes presents this bold documentary, which travels to Roswell, New Mexico in search of answers about legendary UFO sightings.

03059.title: Bomber Boys: The Flying Lancaster
03059.description: A "living history" series reliving the early days of World War II, using a unique blend of living history elements, CGI, first-person interviews and never-before-seen W.W.II footage. This documentary series "Bomber Boys: The Fighting Lancaster" follows a new generation of "Bomber Boys" as they train to become a Lancaster Bomber crew. 7 descendants of World War Two flight crews ready to test themselves against the original training regime of the British Commonwealth Air Training Plan.

0300010296.title: Mysteries at the Museum
0300010296.description: From ghost ships to wooden currency to a presidential cheese wheel, Don Wildman unearths unusual relics from the world's greatest institutions.

0300010299.title: When Ghosts Attack
0300010299.description: Some ghosts go beyond haunting with threats and brutal attacks. This series presents the true stories of people who have dealt with deadly spirits.

03762.title: Animal Miracles
03762.description: Ordinary pets come to the rescue of endangered humans in these miraculous, real-life stories of animals with a touch of the divine.

0918.title: Grime Fighters
0918.description: In our cities, across our countryside an invisible army is fighting a never ending war...The Grime Fighters

0300010310.title: Murder Chose Me
0300010310.description: A seasoned homicide detective uses his interrogation skills to solve murders and catch criminals on the streets of Shreveport, Louisiana.

0300004853.title: Outback Coroner
0300004853.description: Follow coroners as they navigating time, distance, suspicion, and culture in search of answers in the Australian Outback.

04125.title: World War II: Battles Won & Lost
04125.description: Every battle is both a victory and a defeat. It depends which flag you fly. In every theater of the second world war. Battles won and lost determined possesion of territory, of resources and of the strength to go on fighting. For some of the battles it was the victory that most influenced the future course of the war. For others it was the defeat. This is the story of the battles won and lost that decided the outcome of the greatest conflict in history

0300005711.title: The Story of Film: An Odyssey
0300005711.description: The grand evolution of motion pictures is examined and critiqued through the use of film clips and interviews with legendary artists and scholars.

02081.title: My Crazy Ex
02081.description: This docu-reality series tells the extraordinary but true stories of relationships that went awry when one partner’s behavior morphed from romantic to excessive to extreme.

0300007241.title: FOX SOUL's Father's Day Special: From Fatherless to Fatherhood
0300007241.description: A discussion of the challenges of growing up without a father present in the house, and how to do better for the next generation and beyond.

0300009859.title: Life, Death & Money
0300009859.description: This docuseries explores the personal lives, career highlights, and business scandals of A-list celebrities through the money trails they left behind.

0300010319.title: Murder Calls
0300010319.description: Many 911 calls can trigger murder investigations, but can they be trusted? This show reveals how experts decipher an emergency call to find the truth.

02913.title: Women Behind Bars
02913.description: Criminal cases are examined and the perpetrators are profiled in this docuseries, providing a personal and unflinching look at the lives affected.

03773.title: Unsealed Alien Files
03773.description: Investigate released documents regarding alien and UFO encounters, made accessible to the public in 2011 by the Freedom of Information Act. We investigate mass UFO sightings, personal abductions, government cover-ups and breaking alien news from around the world. We delve into the "photoshopping" of space, the value of Wikileaks, and the role social media plays in alien stories.

03403.title: One Born Every Minute UK
03403.description: Every minute of every day, a baby is born in Britain. One Born Every Minute celebrates what it really feels like to become a parent, by taking a bustling maternity hospital and filling it with forty cameras. Filming from the reception desk to the neo-natal ward; from the operating theatre to the birthing pool, this ground-breaking and tender new series observes the dramatic, emotional and often funny moments that go hand in hand with bringing a new life in the world, from the perspective of the soon-to-be parents and family, as well as the hospital staff.

0300007465.title: World's Scariest Hauntings
0300007465.description: Delve into the paranormal universe and travel to ten terrifying locations around the globe, where ghosts and horror stories will keep you up at night.

04717.title: Cosmos: A Spacetime Odyssey
04717.description: Join acclaimed astrophysicist Neil deGrasse Tyson on a journey through space and time in an effort to discover humanity’s place within the universe.

0300004833.title: Breaking the Band
0300004833.description: N.W.A., Fleetwood Mac and the Eagles are among the bands featured in this docuseries exploring the real-life break-ups of popular music groups.

0300000066.title: Lost Civilizations
0300000066.description: Special effects and dramatizations bring to life events and rituals from the Maya, Egyptian, Roman and other ancient cultures and civilizations.

0300006787.title: The Vietnam War: Unknown Images
0300006787.description: A raw and uncensored historical series about The Vietnam War, whose combat-embedded filmed battle footage was previously classified from public view.

0300008470.title: The Joy of Painting With Bob Ross (Español)
0300008470.description: El pintor de árboles felices nos muestra su técnica de mojado sobre mojado y nos anima a plasmar nuestros propios pincelazos sobre el lienzo.

0300000090.title: Victory at Sea
0300000090.description: The Emmy Award-winning series about naval combat during World War II. Famous for its music score, eloquent narration, and combat footage.

0300009653.title: How the Nazis Lost the War
0300009653.description: How Hitler’s dream of dominating Europe was a likely prospect until cracks began to appear among his ranks and his increasingly paranoid mental state.

0300007533.title: Ultimate Countdown
0300007533.description: A trip down celebrity memory lane as the most memorable moments in movies and pop culture are ranked by experts with their own witty insights.

0300008989.title: United by Football: A Season in the USFL
0300008989.description: Follow the inaugural season of the USFL, from the player draft to the thrilling championship, as a league and teams are built from the ground up.

04149.title: World's Most Evil Killers
04149.description: Criminologists, forensic pathologists, federal agents and other experts delve into the lives of the most terrifying and notorious killers in history.

0300007006.title: New Scotland Yard Files
0300007006.description: Hear from some of the most determined detectives in Scotland Yard as they open their files to share exactly how they caught notorious killers.

0300007658.title: Wartime Farm
0300007658.description: Three renowned historians go back in time, over 60 years, to live and survive like real farm families had to in England during World War II.

03137.title: The Presidents - From Politics to Power
03137.description: Who were these great men? How has their leadership shaped the country, government, and way of life we now know today, and what does the future hold for the office of the President of the United States of America? Join us as we examine the lives and times of the men who have defined and re-defined a nation. From George Washington to Barack Obama, discover the political and social legacies of the remarkable men who have presided over the Oval Office!

0300005020.title: Hollywood's Stories
0300005020.description: This docuseries tackles mysterious celebrity deaths, crazy downfalls and all the stories of the rich and famous that everybody wants to know

0300010222.title: A Crime to Remember
0300010222.description: Fashions may change, but these crimes of the past never go out of style. This series looks back at popular murder cases from the ‘50s and '60s.

03582.title: O.J. Speaks: The Hidden Tapes
03582.description: Offering unique access to the civil trial of O.J. Simpson, this special features rare deposition tapes and interviews with the family of Ron Goldman.

0300007970.title: Elite Youth
0300007970.description: America’s most sought-after high school basketball players and future NBA greats compete in the 2018 season of Nike's Elite Youth Basketball League.

04031.title: Universe
04031.description: A visually stunning series with views from the Hubble Space Telescope and NASA’s spacecraft fleet that explores the many mysteries of our universe.

0300008615.title: Fringe Nation
0300008615.description: A look at the fraying seams of America’s dividing lines where fringe voices and actions are nearing an irreversible and disproportionate impact.

0300010311.title: How the World Ends
0300010311.description: This series is an exploration of some of the most noteworthy upcoming predictions of doom and theories that may bring about the end of the world.

0300007227.title: No Go Zones: The World's Toughest Places
0300007227.description: This series reveals what it really means to be part of some of the world's most infamous microcosms. At each location, walk and talk with the people who are part of these communities, who dance with danger every day. Prostitutes, drug dealers, gang member, and police all face different challenges in the same struggle: stay alive or die trying.

0300004896.title: Scandal Made Me Famous
0300004896.description: The unforgettable stories and events that turned everyday people like Casey Anthony, Amy Fisher and Tonya Harding into household names.

0300010309.title: Swamp Murders
0300010309.description: This series reveals the salacious stories behind bodies found in swamps. Featuring reenactments and interviews with people involved in each case.

0300000105.title: Wild Tanzania
0300000105.description: This series showcases the wildlife that inhabit the diverse landscapes of this enthralling African country.

03538.title: Tribes
03538.description: Four tribes in Kenya, detached from the modern world, follow age-old traditions and face desperate challenges as they practice their way of life.

03590.title: I Survived... Beyond and Back
03590.description: Survivors of near-fatal experiences, who returned to life after being pronounced dead, share their stories of what they saw on the other side.

0300008145.title: Great Generals
0300008145.description: This series highlights heroic generals who found battle insights right when it was desperately needed, like American General George S. Patton.

0300000094.title: Blood, Lies and Alibis
0300000094.description: The show follows criminal investigators as they uncover the stories behind brutal killings and deliver justice to families mourning their dead

0300000041.title: The Unknown Story
0300000041.description: This series takes a deep dive into popular films and TV shows, breaking down everything from cast and production, to their impact to global audiences.

04043.title: Crimes That Shook Australia
04043.description: A collection of six documentaries detailing the biggest and most tragic crimes to hit Australia, from the central POV of families, victims and police.

0300004912.title: True CSI
0300004912.description: Examine and solve a murder with the suspense of whodunit and the visceral punch of fly on the wall realism.

0300007747.title: Las Vegas: Secrets Revealed
0300007747.description: Beneath the glittery lights and showbiz facade, Las Vegas offers an important intersection of gaming, commerce, and entertainment.

03122.title: Innovations of War
03122.description:
The Evolution of Tactical Military Weapons

Prepare to be RUSHED INTO THE FIGHT!

The Industrial Revolution of the 18th and 19th Century changed the concept of war and the weapons that could be created for it. Heavy machinery, mass production, and engineering advances allowed for innovative armaments that altered the outcome of battles from the American Civil War to the conflict in Vietnam.

INNOVATIONS OF WAR chronicles the development and deployment of 12 game-changing weapons and the tactical advantage they provided to militaries around the world. Filled with expert interviews, archival footage and live action reenactments, prepare to be RUSHED INTO THE FIGHT!

0300008122.title: True Stories of the American West
0300008122.description: Two fascinating programs tell true stories of the American West and its greatest outlaws and heroes, like Billy the Kid, Jesse James, and Wyatt Earp.

04210.title: Waterloo's Warriors
04210.description: The epic defeat of Napoleon at Waterloo is told from the perspective of the victorious troops, the majority of whom weren’t of English origin.

0300005310.title: Deadly Dates
0300005310.description: True crime series that examines cases of online dating horror stories where innocent singles looking for love were deceived in tragic and fatal ways.

0512.title: Oz and James's Big Wine Adventure
0512.description: Wine expert Oz Clarke invites James May on a month-long trip to France.

0300010397.title: How It's Made
0300010397.description: This series explores the fascinating world of how everyday items are manufactured and produced—anything from toothpicks, to pantyhose, to gummy candy.

0300004863.title: Autopsy: The Last Hours of...
0300004863.description: A docuseries that reveals the truth behind the controversial deaths of global icons whose passings were surrounded by scandal and intense media attention.

0300006537.title: Derren Brown: The Experiments
0300006537.description: The famous psychological illusionist demonstrates how easily our behaviour can be manipulated, and how a simple question can change our entire lives.

0300005257.title: Border Security: Australia's Front Line
0300005257.description: Follow Australia's Immigration, Customs and Quarantine departments as they deal with drug smugglers, illegal immigrants, terrorism and more.

0300005161.title: The Good Girl's Guide to Kinky Sex
0300005161.description: Bucking the notion that only “bad girls” enjoy experimentation, role play, a little intensity, and fun in the bedroom, this show aims to please.

0300009126.title: Unsung
0300009126.description: A documentary series that profiles some of the most influential, talented yet forgotten R&B, Soul and Gospel artists of the 1970s, '80s and '90s.

0300007629.title: Meet, Marry, Murder
0300007629.description: Wedded couples vow to stay together, until death do they part. This series looks at what happens when a bride or groom causes their beloved’s demise.

0300000137.title: Aislados: Una Historia De Supervivencia
0300000137.description: Las islas geográficas han supuesto un laboratorio evolutivo para las especies y un reto para los animales y plantas que se han tenido que adaptar.

0300006079.title: Misterios Sin Revolver
0300006079.description: Entrevistas y recreaciones de crímenes, historias inexplicables y hasta sucesos paranormales que son incógnitas en los expedientes de investigadores.

03127.title: Miracles
03127.description: It has been both an ancient and spiritual question, and today a question of science: What are these miraculous events? ... Where do they come from? ... And what do they mean? ... If miracles are real, are they divine intervention and what is the role of spirituality, religion and prayer?  This 4-part series explores and investigates the many answers to these questions through interviews with theologians, historians, experts, actual witnesses and visits to the locations where it is believed some of the most beautiful and profound miracles occurred.
